{
  "name": "ExploreEQA on HM-EQA",
  "description": "Prismatic-VLM exploration over HM3D scenes for House-Mesh Embodied Question Answering (Ren et al. 2024, explore-eqa). Each step: RGB-D \u2192 TSDF fusion \u2192 VLM answer-probability (A/B/C/D) + relevancy (Y/N) \u2192 visual-prompt frontier points, LSV+GSV VLM score \u2192 frontier-weighted next-pose \u2192 free-pose teleport. Post-hoc weighted vote over the trajectory emits the final letter. The Prismatic VLM is decoupled into the generic ``vlm_prismatic`` foundation-model nodeset (separate hmeqa subprocess); the four per-step VLM calls \u2014 pred A/B/C/D, rel Yes/No, frontier LSV, frontier GSV \u2014 are explicit ``vlm_prismatic__score_tokens`` instances wired between explore_eqa pre/post nodes. step_budget is set per-episode by the framework from the env's env-panel on_load() return: int(sqrt(scene_size)*3) per Ren et al. 2024 \u00a7VI (~85 max for ~800 m\u00b2 scenes). The graph-level step_budget below is a failsafe ceiling; env_hmeqa__step.done now fires only on env-side error (bad action / sim failure).",
